{
  "texts": [
    "While LLMs can generate a wide range of responses, they often produce inaccuracies, biases, or contradictions, especially when dealing with carefully crafted prompts.",
    "Despite these shortcomings, LLMs can still enhance education if used strategically.",
    "Educators can design tasks that encourage students to critically evaluate AI-generated content, identify errors, and deepen their understanding of scientific concepts.",
    "LLMs should be viewed as tools to complement traditional teaching methods, not to replace them.",
    "In conclusion, LLMs have the potential to enrich educational experiences when integrated thoughtfully, with educators playing a crucial role in guiding their use to promote deeper engagement and critical thinking."
  ]
}